{"title_page": "Praanam", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{more citations needed|date=December 2012}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Praanam\n| image = Pranam 2003.jpg\n| writer = Subba Rao Master\n| starring = [[Allari Naresh]]<br>[[Sadha]]<br>[[Seetha (actress)|Seetha]]<br>[[Rajan P. Dev]]<br>Shafi\n| director = Malli\n| cinematography = Bharani Dharan\n| producer = Maganti Babu\n| editing = Basva Paidireddy\n| distributor = GMRC\n| country = India\n| released = 25 July 2003\n| runtime =\n| language = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| music = Kamalakar\n| awards =\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n\n'''''Praanam''''' is a 2003 [[Telugu language|Telugu]] [[fantasy film|fantasy]] [[romantic drama film]] starring [[Allari Naresh]] and [[Sadha]] in the Lead directed by Malli. The film was released on 25 July 2003. The movie was based on the concept of [[Reincarnation]].<ref name=\"Bhashyam Ajay\">{{cite web|last1=Bhashyam|first1=Ajay|title=Praanam review|url=http://movies.fullhyderabad.com/praanam/telugu/praanam-movie-reviews-944-2.html|website=movies.fullhyderabad.com|publisher=Fullhyderabad.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThen there was a village in coastal area. Sivudu ([[Allari Naresh]]) 26 belongs to lower caste and Katyayani ([[Sadha]]) 23 is a chaste Brahmin. When the village head 50 (also Sadha's strict Brahmin father) played by Mantripragada Venkat Rao comes to know that they fell in love, he decides to hang them off because inter-caste love/marriage is a sin as per their village laws and the consequences behind previous experiences regarding inter-caste love. These two souls take a rebirth. Kathyayani is born as Uma 21, a sister of powerful politician (Benerjee) 39. Sivudu is born as Kaasi 23, a NRI orphan who returns from USA (Los Angeles, California) to do a Telugu music video album. He is in search of a pristine Telugu girl and he finds Uma. They fall in love, but her politician brother wants her to marry his nephew (Shafi) (also known as his brother-in-law's son) 22. Uma and Kaasi run away from Vizag city to coastal area and incidentally they land in a place where Kathyayani and Sivudu lived. The village men identify them. The rest of the film is all about how all ends well.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Allari Naresh]] as Sivudu / Kaasi\n*[[Sadha]] as Katyayani / Uma\n*[[Seetha (actress)|Seetha]] as Sivudu's mother\n* Mantripragada Venkat Rao as Katyayani's (Sadha) strict Brahmin father\n*[[Rajan P. Dev]] in a special appearance\n*[[Banerjee (actor)|Banerjee]] as Uma's brother\n*[[Shafi (actor)|Shafi]] as Uma's brother's nephew\n*[[Anitha Chowdary]]\n*[[Rallapalli (actor)|Rallapalli]]\n*[[M. S. Narayana]]\n*[[Kovai Sarala]]\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Praanam\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Kamalakar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Album cover\n| released   =\n| recorded   = 2002\u20132003\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack]]\n| length     =\n| label      = Supreme Music\n| producer   = Kamalakar\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\nThe film features Music by Kamalakar. The lyrics were penned by Sri Sai Harsha, Suddala Ashok Teja and E. S. Murthy.In this film ''Nindu Noorella, song was highly super hit....''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:70%;\"\n|-\n! Song Title !! Singers !! Lyricist\n|-\n| ''Nindu Noorella'' || [[Sonu Nigam]], [[Mahalakshmi Iyer]] || [[Sai Sriharsha]]\n|-\n| ''Sayyari Na Yenki''|| [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]] || Sri Sai Harsha\n|-\n| ''Snehama Swapnama'' || [[Hariharan (singer)|Hariharan]], [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]] || [[Sai Sriharsha]]\n|-\n| ''Vaatapi'' || [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]] || E. S. Murthy\n|-\n| ''Bramhandam'' || [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]] || [[Sai Sriharsha]]\n|-\n| ''Nindu Noorella \u2013 2'' || Kamalakar, [[Gopika Poornima]] || [[Sai Sriharsha]]\n|-\n| ''Dhim Dhim Dhim'' || [[Shankar Mahadevan]], Kalpana || [[Suddala Ashok Teja]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|1285133}}\n\n[[Category:2000s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:2003 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n\n\n{{2000s-Telugu-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{more citations needed|date=December 2012}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Praanam\n| image = Pranam 2003.jpg\n| writer = Subba Rao Master\n| starring = [[Allari Naresh]]<br>[[Sadha]]<br>[[Seetha (actress)|Seetha]]<br>[[Rajan P. Dev]]<br>Shafi\n| director = Malli\n| cinematography = Bharani Dharan\n| producer = Maganti Babu\n| editing = Basva Paidireddy\n| distributor = GMRC\n| country = India\n| released = 25 July 2003\n| runtime =\n| language = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| music = Kamalakar\n| awards =\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n\n'''''Praanam''''' is a 2003 [[Telugu language|Telugu]] [[fantasy film|fantasy]] [[romantic drama film]] starring [[Allari Naresh]] and [[Sadha]] in the Lead directed by Malli. The film was released on 25 July 2003. The movie was based on the concept of [[Reincarnation]].<ref name=\"Bhashyam Ajay\">{{cite web|last1=Bhashyam|first1=Ajay|title=Praanam review|url=http://movies.fullhyderabad.com/praanam/telugu/praanam-movie-reviews-944-2.html|website=movies.fullhyderabad.com|publisher=Fullhyderabad.com|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThen there was a village in coastal area. Sivudu ([[Allari Naresh]]) 26 belongs to lower caste and Katyayani ([[Sadha]]) 23 is a chaste Brahmin. When the village head 50 (also Sadha's strict Brahmin father) played by Mantripragada Venkat Rao comes to know that they fell in love, he decides to hang them off because inter-caste love/marriage is a sin as per their village laws and the consequences behind previous experiences regarding inter-caste love. These two souls take a rebirth. Kathyayani is born as Uma 21, a sister of powerful politician (Benerjee)39. Sivudu is born as Kaasi 23, a NRI orphan who returns from USA (Los Angeles, California) to do a Telugu music video album. He is in search of a pristine Telugu girl and he finds Uma. They fall in love, but her politician brother wants her to get married to his nephew(Shafi) (also known as his brother-in-law's son) 22. Uma and Kaasi run away from Vizag city to coastal area and incidentally they land in a place where Kathyayani and Sivudu lived. The village men identify them. The rest of the film is all about how all ends well.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Allari Naresh]] as Sivudu / Kaasi\n*[[Sadha]] as Katyayani / Uma\n*[[Seetha (actress)|Seetha]] as Sivudu's Mother\n* Mantripragada Venkat Rao as Katyayani's (Sadha) Strict Brahmin Father\n*[[Rajan P. Dev]] in a Special Appearance\n*[[Banerjee (actor)|Banerjee]] as Uma's Brother\n*[[Shafi (actor)|Shafi]] as Uma's Brother's Nephew\n*[[Anitha Chowdary]]\n*[[Rallapalli (actor)|Rallapalli]]\n*[[M. S. Narayana]]\n*[[Kovai Sarala]]\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Praanam\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Kamalakar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Album cover\n| released   =\n| recorded   = 2002\u20132003\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack]]\n| length     =\n| label      = Supreme Music\n| producer   = Kamalakar\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\nThe film features Music by Kamalakar. The lyrics were penned by Sri Sai Harsha, Suddala Ashok Teja and E. S. Murthy.In this film ''Nindu Noorella, song was highly super hit....''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:70%;\"\n|-\n! Song Title !! Singers !! Lyricist\n|-\n| ''Nindu Noorella'' || [[Sonu Nigam]], [[Mahalakshmi Iyer]] || [[Sai Sriharsha]]\n|-\n| ''Sayyari Na Yenki''|| [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]] || Sri Sai Harsha\n|-\n| ''Snehama Swapnama'' || [[Hariharan (singer)|Hariharan]], [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]] || [[Sai Sriharsha]]\n|-\n| ''Vaatapi'' || [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]] || E. S. Murthy\n|-\n| ''Bramhandam'' || [[S. P. Balas