ersen]]|DEN|{{ct|SUN|2020}}|8|[[File:Jersey yellow number.svg|20px]]}}\n{{cyclingresult|8|[[Jos\u00e9 Manuel D\u00edaz (cyclist)|Jos\u00e9 Manuel D\u00edaz]]|ESP|{{ct|DMP|2020}}|7}}\n{{cyclingresult|9|[[Vincenzo Nibali]]|ITA|{{ct|TFS|2020}}|6}}\n{{cyclingresult|10|[[Thibaut Pinot]]|FRA|{{ct|GFC|2020}}|6}}\n{{cyclingresult end}}\n{{column}}\n{{columns-end}}\n{{columns-start}}\n\n===Young rider classification===\n{{cyclingresult start|title=Final young rider classification (1\u20139)<ref name=\"Result-S7\" /><ref name=\"PN-ranks\" />}}\n{{cyclingresult|1|[[Sergio Higuita]]|COL|{{ct|EFD|2020}}|22h 47' 25\"|[[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]]}}\n{{cyclingresult|2|[[Aur\u00e9lien Paret-Peintre]]|FRA|{{ct|ALM|2020}}|+ 15' 28\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|3|[[Kasper Asgreen]]|DEN|{{ct|QST|2020}}|+ 25' 57\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|4|[[Cees Bol]]|NED|{{ct|SUN|2020}}|+ 31' 02\"|[[File:Jersey yellow number.svg|20px]]}}\n{{cyclingresult|5|[[Connor Swift]]|GBR|{{ct|FST|2020}}|+ 38' 48\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|6|[[Jos\u00e9 Manuel D\u00edaz (cyclist)|Jos\u00e9 Manuel D\u00edaz]]|ESP|{{ct|DMP|2020}}|+ 39' 14\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|7|[[Chris Hamilton (cyclist)|Chris Hamilton]]|AUS|{{ct|SUN|2020}}|+ 43' 02\"|[[File:Jersey yellow number.svg|20px]]}}\n{{cyclingresult|8|[[Piet Allegaert]]|BEL|{{ct|COF|2020}}|+ 50' 56\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|9|[[Cyril Barthe]]|FRA|{{ct|VCB|2020}}|+ 54' 24\"}}\n{{cyclingresult end}}\n{{column}}\n===Teams classification===\n{{cyclingresult start|title=Final teams classification (1\u201310)<ref name=\"Result-S7\" /><ref name=\"PN-ranks\" />|rider=no}}\n{{cyclingresult|1|||{{ct|SUN|2020}} [[File:Jersey yellow number.svg|20px]]|81h 52' 39\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|2|||{{ct|GFC|2020}}|+ 3' 25\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|3|||{{ct|TFS|2020}}|+ 9' 19\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|4|||{{ct|LTS|2020}}|+ 15' 31\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|5|||{{ct|EFD|2020}}|+ 19' 17\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|6|||{{ct|QST|2020}}|+ 21' 06\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|7|||{{ct|BOH|2020}}|+ 24' 38\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|8|||{{ct|WGG|2020}}|+ 30' 51\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|9|||{{ct|ALM|2020}}|+ 33' 41\"}}\n{{cyclingresult|10|||{{ct|FST|2020}}|+ 43' 03\"}}\n{{cyclingresult end}}\n{{columns-end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Paris\u2013Nice}}\n{{2020 UCI World Tour}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Paris-Nice, 2020}}\n[[Category:Paris\u2013Nice|2020]]\n[[Category:2020 UCI World Tour]]\n[[Category:2020 in French sport]]\n[[Category:March 2020 sports events in France]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Cycling race}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox cycling race report\n| name               = 2020 Paris\u2013Nice\n| series             = [[2020 UCI World Tour]]\n| race_no            = \n| season_no          = \n| image              = \n| image_caption      = \n| image_size         = \n| date               = 8\u201314 March 2020<ref group=\"nb\">The race was initially scheduled to be held between 8-15 March 2020, but was shortened in order to fight the spread of the [[SARS-CoV-2]] virus, responsible for the [[Coronavirus disease 2019]].</ref>\n| stages             = 7<ref group=\"nb\">The race was initially due to have 8 stages, but the last stage was cancelled to fight the spread of the [[SARS-CoV-2]] virus, responsible for the [[Coronavirus disease 2019]].</ref>\n| distance           = 1122.1\n| unit               = km\n| time               = 27h 14' 23\"\n| speed              = \n| first              = [[Maximilian Schachmann]]\n| first_nat          = GER\n| first_team         = {{ct|BOH|2020}}\n| first_color        = yellow\n| second             = [[Tiesj Benoot]]\n| second_nat         = BEL\n| second_team        = {{ct|SUN|2020}}\n| third              = [[Sergio Higuita]]\n| third_nat          = COL\n| third_team         = {{ct|EFD|2020}}\n| points             = [[Tiesj Benoot]]\n| points_nat         = BEL\n| points_team        = {{ct|SUN|2020}}\n| points_color       = green\n| mountains          = [[Nicolas Edet]]\n| mountains_nat      = FRA\n| mountains_team     = {{ct|COF|2020}}\n| mountains_color    = polkadot\n| youth              = [[Sergio Higuita]]\n| youth_nat          = COL\n| youth_team         = {{ct|EFD|2020}}\n| youth_color        = white\n| team               = {{ct|SUN|2020}}\n| previous           = [[2019 Paris\u2013Nice|2019]]\n| next               =\n}}\nThe '''2020 Paris\u2013Nice''' was a [[road cycling]] [[cycling stage race|stage race]] that was held between 8 and 14 March 2020 in France. It was the 78th edition of [[Paris\u2013Nice]] and the fifth race of the [[2020 UCI World Tour]]. The race was shortened on 13 March, removing the final stage, due to concerns over the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. The global health situation had already led to the withdrawal of several teams before and during the race.\n\n==Teams==\nSeventeen teams participated in the race, including twelve [[UCI WorldTour]] teams and five [[UCI Professional Continental]] teams. Several teams originally scheduled to take part in the race withdrew due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], incluuding {{ct|AST|2020}}, {{ct|BMC|2020}}, {{ct|MTS men|2020}}, {{ct|MOV|2020}}, {{ct|INS|2020}}, {{ct|TLJ|2020}}, and {{ct|UAD|2020}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paris-nice.fr/en/news/2020/teams-selected-for-2020-paris-nice/17232|title=Teams selected for 2020 Paris\u2013Nice|date=7 January 2020|accessdate=9 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cyclingweekly.com/news/latest-news/paris-nice-start-list-214099|title=Paris-Nice 2020 start list: Top riders start despite Coronavirus fears|work=Cycling Weekly|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cyclingnews.com/features/coronavirus-team-withdrawal-tracker/|title=Coronavirus: Team withdrawal tracker|work=cyclingnews|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=6 March 2020}}</ref> During the race, many riders and teams chose to pull out, including {{ct|TBM|2020}}, {{ct|ISN|2020}}, and defending world road race champion [[Mads Pedersen (cyclist)|Mads Pedersen]], due to various coronavirus-related reasons.<ref name=\"TBM\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cyclingnews.com/news/teams-pull-out-of-paris-nice-over-coronavirus-concerns/|title=Bahrain-McLaren pull out of Paris-Nice over coronavirus concerns|first=Stephen|last=Farrand|publisher=CyclingNews|date=13 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cyclingnews.com/news/coronavirus-world-champion-mads-pedersen-leaves-paris-nice/|title=Coronavirus: World champion Mads Pedersen leaves Paris-Nice|first=Daniel|last=Ostanek|publisher=CyclingNews|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref> As a result, of the 136 riders who started the race, only 61 riders finished.\n\n'''UCI WorldTeams'''\n{{div col|colwidth=20em|style=margin-right:20%;}}\n* {{ct|ALM|2020}}\n* {{ct|TBM|2020}}\n* {{ct|BOH|2020}}\n* {{ct|COF|2020}}\n* {{ct|QST|2020}}\n* {{ct|EFD|2020}}\n* {{ct|GFC|2020}}\n* {{ct|ISN|2020}}\n* {{ct|LTS|2020}}\n* {{ct|NTT|2020}}\n* {{ct|SUN|2020}}\n* {{ct|TFS|2020}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''UCI Professional Continental teams'''\n{{div col|colwidth=20em|style=margin-right:20%;}}\n* {{ct|FST|2020}}\n* {{ct|VCB|2020}}\n* {{ct|WGG|2020}}\n* {{ct|DMP|2020}}\n* {{ct|TDE|2020}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Route==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Stage characteristics and winners<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.paris-nice.fr/en/overall-route|title=Route of Paris\u2013Nice 2020|work=[[Paris\u2013Nice]]|publisher=[[Amaury Sport Organisation]]|accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Stage\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Course\n! scope=\"col\" | Distance\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Type\n! scope=col | Winner\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[#Stage 1|1]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 8 March\n| [[Plaisir]] to Plaisir\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{convert|154|km|abbr=on}}\n| [[File:Hillystage.svg|20px|link=|alt=]]\n| Hi